after: BAE Systems plays a significant role in the production of military equipment. In 2008, 95% of BAE Systems' total sales were military related.[101][102]

It plays important roles in military aircraft production. The company's Typhoon fighter and Tornado fighter-bomber are both front line aircraft of the RAF.[103] The company is a major partner in the F-35 Lightning II programme.[104] Its Hawk advanced jet trainer aircraft has been widely exported.[105] In July 2006, the British government declassified the HERTI (High Endurance Rapid Technology Insertion), an Unmanned Aerial Vehicle (UAV) which can navigate autonomously.[106]
